      <item>
        <title>Port to Sequoia-PGP (&quot;sq&quot;) (GnuPG (&quot;gpg&quot;) replacement) - OpenPGP</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Kicksecure, and Whonix have been ported from GnuPG (<code>"gpg</code>") to Sequoia-PGP (“<code>sq</code>”).</p>
<aside class="quote" data-post="2" data-topic="1638">
  <div class="title">
    <div class="quote-controls"></div>
    <img alt="" width="24" height="24" src="https://forums.kicksecure.com/user_avatar/forums.kicksecure.com/patrick/48/165_2.png" class="avatar">
    <div class="quote-title__text-content">
      <a href="https://forums.kicksecure.com/t/sequoia-git-sq-git/1638/2">Sequoia git (`sq-git`)</a> <a class="badge-category__wrapper " href="https://forums.kicksecure.com/c/development/7"><span data-category-id="7" style="--category-badge-color: #25AAE2; --category-badge-text-color: #FFF;" data-drop-close="true" class="badge-category --style-square " title="Development of Kicksecure software and source code. Development Discussion Policy and First-Time Source Code Contributor Policy apply."><span class="badge-category__name">Development</span></span></a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <blockquote>
    <a href="https://www.kicksecure.com/wiki/Dev/Derivative-Maker" class="inline-onebox">Derivative-Maker - Debian based Linux Bootable Image Builder</a>, which is used to create packages and images for Kicksecure (and Whonix) images, is now using Sequoia git (“sq-git”). 
As far as images are concerned, this is applicable to non-Qubes only. 
Note: Qubes images are built using Qubes builder, not derivative-maker.
  </blockquote>
</aside>

<p>Reasons:</p>
<ul>
<li>The APT package manager has been ported to sqv as of Debian trixie.</li>
<li>The RPM package manager was ported to Sequoia.</li>
<li>Qubes builder infrastructure uses sequoia.</li>
<li><a href="https://gpg.fail/">https://gpg.fail/</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.kicksecure.com/wiki/OpenPGP#Issues_with_PGP">Issues with PGP</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.kicksecure.com/wiki/OpenPGP#GnuPG_Usability_Security_Issues">GnuPG Usability Security Issues</a></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p>Therefore, <a href="https://github.com/Kicksecure/gpg-bash-lib">gpg-bash-lib</a> is no longer in use</p>
          <p><a href="https://forums.kicksecure.com/t/port-to-sequoia-pgp-sq-gnupg-gpg-replacement-openpgp/260/18">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
